//WHAT IS POLYMORPHISM AND WHAT ARE ITS TYPES? ‚ùñ      
Polymorphism is the ability of a variable, object, or function to take on MULTIPLE FORMS. 
What is multiple forms? For example, in English ‚ÄúRUNNING‚Äù word can be used for ‚Äúrunning a race‚Äù or ‚Äúrunning a business‚Äù. 
In both cases the meaning is different but the name ‚ÄúRUNNING‚Äù is same.

///Overloading (compile time check)
//class Employee
