My Friend: DSA is tough.
Me: Not for me. I follow the 3-7-15 Rule. 
But let me be honest ‚Äî
It wasn‚Äôt always this way.
I used to forget what I solved just a week ago.
The problem wasn‚Äôt practice.
It was retention.
That‚Äôs when I created the 3-7-15 Rule üëá

Solve a question 4 times:
‚úÖ First time ‚Äî Understand and solve it
‚úÖ After 3 days ‚Äî Solve it again to remember
‚úÖ After 7 days ‚Äî Solve it once more to get better
‚úÖ After 15 days ‚Äî Solve it one last time to make it stick in your mind
By the 4th time, your brain stops panicking.
You recognize patterns instantly.

